reviewText:
+excellent shooting experience;
+guns with multiple ammunition types adds a significant amount of variety to fights;
+some (rather) memorable locations;
+sound effects;
+graphics (artistic);

-storyline;
-no proper rewards for completing optional tasks;
-exploration is not rewarding at all;
-racing is repetitive as hell;
-liniar;
-artificially increased playtime - you need to drive empty ♥♥♥ canyons to reach your next mission location;
-the campaign doesn't give you the feeling that you're part of something bigger;
-the game world is small for a game that advertises itself as an open world experience;
-very few locations with missions sending you back and forth between these zones;
-one of the worst/most unsatisfying endings of any games I played till the end;
-graphics (technical);
-framerate cap (60fps);
-mouse movement in menus is an absolute curse;

Rage is an excellent shooter, but unfortunately a very limited experience overall with very few moments to make it worthwhile.
